cs.CR, cs.DB, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.IT 

This paper deals with privacy-preserving data perturbation and missing data imputation, which are common topics in the fields of cryptography (cs.CR), databases (cs.DB), machine learning (cs.LG), data science (cs.DS), and information theory (cs.IT). However, given the focus on privacy and data perturbation, cs.CR and cs.DB are the most likely categories, followed by cs.LG, cs.DS, and cs.IT.
